# Lab: Basic SSRF Against Local Server

## Vulnerability
Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) - Server makes HTTP requests to URLs controlled by attacker

## Target
- Stock check feature that fetches data from internal URLs
- Admin panel only accessible from loopback (127.0.0.1/localhost)

## Attack Steps
1. Found vulnerable `stockApi` parameter in stock form
2. Changed value from legitimate URL to: `http://localhost/admin?username=carlos`
3. Server made request to localhost (treated as trusted)
4. Server accessed admin panel and deleted user carlos

## Why It Worked
- Server blindly makes requests to any URL in stockApi parameter
- No validation of target URLs
- Localhost requests treated as trusted (internal)
- Attacker can access restricted internal services

## Impact
- Access to admin interface
- Delete users
- Potentially access sensitive data
